I first visited Via Carducci on Easter Sunday 2019. Being from the suburbs I’m not as familiar with the “downtown” restaurants as I am those in the Western suburbs; places like Oak Park, Melrose Park, etc., both of which are very well known for their high-end and authentic cuisines. So when my longtime Sicilian friend Martinu immediately suggested Via Carducci I trusted his Chicago-based opinion.  I was not disappointed.  What a magnificent gem of a Traditional Italian Ristorante! From the authenticity of its non-ostentatious surroundings and excellent service to some of the best Southern Italian menu offerings, I must say that I was unaware that places like this were still around. The photos tell a story that I cannot convey in words. Please just place it on your “must visit” list. You will not be disappointed either!

(Translated by Google) Sunday brunch! what is it and how does it happen?  It is believed that the concept of "brunch" was coined by Lewis Carroll (English Lewis Carroll, real name Charles Dodgson Dodgson, or Charles Latwidge Dodgson, Charles Lutwidge Dodgson). The writer combined the words breakfast and lunch and sent a letter to the rector of Oxford University asking him to put brunch on the agenda. Brunch soon became a new tradition in Oxford, and then throughout England. The most common place for Sunday family gatherings are fashionable establishments.  In the establishment, the preparation of the menu for brunches does not take much time, three or four days. The range varies depending on the season and seasonal products, as well as the availability of suppliers. "Specials" are prepared for each brunch - several special dishes, often of one theme. For such positions, the institution has the opportunity to order products in a couple of weeks, in advance. The main dishes can be guinea fowl from France, which are baked entirely with oranges, rosemary and thyme, roast beef, cooked at a temperature of 85 degrees with garlic and thyme, as well as Yorkshire pudding.  An important condition for brunch is a variety of dishes, as it is often a family pastime or in the company of friends, and the position should satisfy the choice of each guest. There are no strict restrictions in the range, but the mandatory items are still regulated: salads, snacks, meat and fish dishes and, of course, desserts, as guests spend several hours in the restaurant. Brunch, in essence, is a fairly late breakfast that turns into lunch.  It is important for the chef to show his creative side, to surprise the guests so that they have a desire to try all the presented dishes. Submission and design is an important aspect of the presentation.  Active preparation for Brunch begins in two days. On Friday marinades, preparation of products and preparations for desserts (biscuits, for example). The main preparations end on Saturday evening or Sunday morning. In the morning, for example, bread is baked, which should be at least three types - light and dark baguette, baguette with dark chocolate or dor blue cheese, ciabatta with ham and sun-dried tomatoes.  The amount of food in grams or kilograms of food is not calculated because it is not a banquet. And the concept of brunch is unlimited access to food and drink.  The menu is quite diverse 6-10 salads, 12-15 different snacks, 8-10 hot dishes, land station, 8-12 desserts.  All dishes are divided into stations: grill corner with 5 types of meat, fish and vegetarian items that will be cooked to your liking on the grill, local food - Olivier, "Fur coat", forshmak and pancakes with caviar, desserts: a few tartu, cheesecake, macarons, Miss Cott, rum cake, creme brulee, truffles, handmade candies, etc. Additionally, there may be other a la carte dishes, such as oysters.  The undisputed hit is the sushi station. The range includes 8 types: poppies, rolls and sushi.  In addition to the waiters, brunch serves about 9 staff members.  Naturally, some products remain intact. If these are blanks in the refrigerator - they are used in the future. If these are dishes from the buffet, they are disposed of.  There are no strict rules, a dress code for brunches, but it is desirable - business / smart casual. The main thing is to enjoy communicating with family and friends. Not only sound food but his alertness and dedication too are most required. Decent musical accompaniment, such as professional pianists.  (Original) Недільний бранч! що це таке і як це відбувається?  Вважається, що поняття «бранч» придумав сам Льюїс Керролл (англ. Lewis Carroll, справжнє ім'я Чарльз Доджсон Доджсон, або Чарльз Латуідж Доджсон, Charles Lutwidge Dodgson). Письменник об'єднав слова breakfast і lunch і відправив лист ректору Оксфордського університету з проханням ввести в розпорядок дня brunch. Незабаром бранч став новою традицією Оксфорда, а потім і всієї Англії. Найчастішим місцем недільних сімейних зустрічей стають фешенебельні заклади.  У закладі погдготовка меню для бранчів займає не так багато часу три, чотири дні. Асортимент змінюється в залежності від сезону і сезонних продуктів, а також від доступності постачальників. На кожен бранч готується «specials» - кілька особливих страв, частіше однієї тематики. Для таких позицій у закладу є можливість замовити продукти за пару тижнів, завчасно. Основними стравами можуть бути цесарки з Франції, які запікалися цілком з апельсинами, розмарином і чебрецем, ростбіф, приготований при температурі 85 градусів з часником і чебрецем, а також йоркширський пудинг.  Важлива умова для бранча - це різноманітність блюд, оскільки найчастіше це сімейне проведення часу або ж в компанії друзів, і позиції повинні задовольнити вибір кожного гостя. Строгих обмежень в асортименті немає, але обов'язкові позиції все ж регламентовані: салати, закуски, м'ясні і рибні страви і, звичайно ж, десерти, оскільки гості проводять в закладі кілька годин. Бранч, за своєю суттю - це досить пізній сніданок, що переходить в обід.  Шеф-кухарю важливо показати свою творчу сторону, здивувати гостей, щоб у них виникло бажання спробувати всі представлені страви. Подача і оформлення - важлива сторона презентації.  Активна підготовка до Бранчу починається за два дні. У п'ятницю маринади, підготовка продуктів і заготовки до десертів (бісквіти, наприклад). Основні приготування закінчуються в суботу ввечері або ж у неділю вранці. Вранці, наприклад, випікається хліб, якого повинно бути не менше трьох видів - світлий і темний багет, багет з чорним шоколадом або сиром дор блю, чіабатта з шинкою і в'яленими томатами.  Кількість їжі в грамах або кілограмах їжі не розраховуються, оскільки це не банкет. І концепція бранча складається в безлімітному доступі до їжі і напоїв.  Меню досить різноманітне 6-10 салатів, 12-15 різних закусок, 8-10 гарячих страв, станція суші, 8-12 десертів.  Всі страви розбиті по станціях: гриль-корнер з 5-ма видами м'яса, риби і вегетаріанських позицій, які приготують по твоєму смаку на грилі, local food - олів'є, «Шуба», форшмак і млинці з ікрою, десерти: кілька Тарту, чізкейк, макаронс, панна Котта, ромовий кекс, крем брюле, трюфеля, цукерки ручної роботи та ін. Додатково можуть бути інші страви a la carte, наприклад, устриці.  Безперечний хіт - це суші станція. Асортимент включає 8 видів: маки, роли і суші.  Крім офіціантів, бранч обслуговує близько 9 чоловік персоналу.  Закономірно, частина продуктів залишається незайманою. Якщо це заготовки в холодильнику - вони використовуються в подальшому. Якщо це страви з буфету, вони утілізірются.  Строгих правил, дрес-коду для бранчів немає, але желателен- business / smart casual. Головне, це отримувати задоволення від спілкування з сім'єю, друзями. Важлива не тільки їжа, але і атмосфера. Гідне музичний супровід, наприклад професійні піаністи.

The pizza, pasta, and appetizers are all phenomenal. If you can only visit one or two places in West Town you should check out Via Carducci.

Hands down worst pizza I've ever had. Arrived in such a mess, chewy horrible base, way too much parmesan.  Overpowered not only the flavour but permeated every room in the house. Had one bite and took out to the trash.  Burnt flavourless garlic bread, sloppy liquefied mashed potatoes. Marinara sauce is truly bland. How can you mess up such a simple order? Waste of money
Wery nice place with nice atmosphere Friendly staff Good selection of domestic and imported beer Tasty pizza and desert Everything that Italian restaurant should have
Always really good food! I bring friends and family here.
Great Italian Restaurant.
Love everything!
Authentic Italian food at reasonable prices.  Great atmosphere (especially with the live music outside!)
An old school Italian trattoria in Wicker Park.  Easy to overlook in up and coming neighborhood.   A reasonable meal at a reasonable price
Overall, the food is always delicious, the space very comfortable, and the owners and entire staff are very friendly and personable! Great place!

Been coming here since they opened. Never, ever disappointed.  Our appetizer go to is the eggplant with goat cheese.  I've tried all of the pasta dishes. The atmosphere is lovely and have seen some wonderful Italian musicians from time to time.  Especially like the summer months, eating out on the sidewalk on division, taking in the wicker park sites.  Even bring my dogs for dinner.  I'll let them wrote their own review!!!
Tried something new here and was not disappointed. A huge variety of specials for an adventurous palette.
The pizza as a dine-in and a carry out option is fantastic.   One of the best in the neighborhood.  The rest of the menu is great.
Fresh delicious food, great service
Cozy Italian restaurant. Great service and food
Great food, drinks, and people.

Every time I've gone here it's amazing. I've had 8 different pastas here and they have all been very tasty. The space is also small and intimate, which gives this place a great atmosphere.
The best tiramisu!!! They make it fresh everyday!!!!!!
Fancy, great food, loved the tiramisu as well as my Cosmpolitan. Make reservations and don't expect a lot of moving space -- tables are pretty close to each other.
This restaurant is the best to eat nice dinner and  relax
Great Menu and very comfortable  atmosphere.
Excellent pizza. Thin crust ambrosia. Italian dishes follow suit.  Haven't had anything bad yet. 5 stars in a 4 star world.
Tremendous food, wonderful service and great ambiance.
had beef carpaccio once.. and everytime i ask if they will have it again they tell me next week on the new menu.. sweet that they lie like that.
Very delicious Italian food! Nice and quite place.
My girlfriend and I came here on a Tuesday evening to celebrate her birthday. This particular night they had wine tasting and a live band playing. It was such a great vibe and the food was amazing!

Absolutely delicious food. We had the fried calamari, bufala and prosciutto, carbonara, and rotini, sharing everything amongst three people. Staff was wonderful, wine was amazing and affordable. All things great, and coming back soon! Well done.
Tasty but slightly overpriced.

Good server, food was served quick, so quick that my gf barely drank any of her wine.  Food was good though. Special was sea bass, I asked the waiter if it was ill tempered, he didn't get it...but it was still funny.  (If you don't get the reference, look it up)
Great food with great chat from the waiter
Great food. Good service. Best bathrooms.

Service depends on who you get, been here a handful of times where I know if it's going to be good service or not.  So you're rolling the dice with your waiter.  The food is the same, it depends on what you get.  Some meals are outstanding and hit all 9,000 taste buds while others lack and have very little flavor.  Definitely a place I'm not dying to go to again but it's nice and fair on the wallet.  Small environment is probably the best aspect of this place, good for a first date that can be casual intimate.
A smaller but equally solid outpost of a high quality local chain.

Fantastic food and sangria! Prices weren't too bad, I typically expect to pay a bit more when I go to an Italian restaurant anyways. They even have a nice size sidewalk patio. They were pretty busy when I went for dinner, so expect to have a short wait... Maybe larger if you're dining on their outdoor patio.
We randomly came here today and I am very glad that we did! The food was excellent and the service was great. The price is a bargain for the quality of food too. We will be coming back again soon!
child friendly for early dinner, good atmosphere, friendly, accommodating service

Traditional Italian place with big menu.  They serve pizza, pasta, sandwiches and specialty dishes. Prices and portions are fair.  I usually get the eggplant parm or penne arriabiata and they are always good.  Most of the times they are accommodating and let me add extra vegetables.  Appetizers are pretty small and overpriced.  Wine selection is good but beer selection is very weak.

Classic Italian restaurant with an intimate atmosphere. The selection of wine they have is amazing. I haven't tried a past dish there that I did not love. The salads are pretty tasty as well - I usually don't order salad at an Italian place. Great place for a data or small group gatherings.

The restaurant is close to my home, the atmosphere is classy and lots of happy people.  The greeters are personable, and no waiting for a great seat.  Apetizers are delicious with a large menu to choose from.  I could stop at the salad, bur I didn't it's finger licking good.  The entree that each of us had was superb and the desert was the icing on the cake.  I have had the delivery and it is fast and efficient with bread, butter, salad and entree.  Great customer service.
This is a wonderful restaurant for a date. They have great Italian food, namely the veal and the frutte de mare pasta. Good wine selection, all in a very cozy, intimate setting.
